sum(if(id is null or id = '', 0, 1)) / sum(1) id_coverage,
sum(if(cmsId is null or id = '', 0, 1)) / sum(1) cmsId_coverage,
sum(if(series_name is null or id = '', 0, 1)) / sum(1) series_name_coverage,
sum(if(season_number is null or id = '', 0, 1)) / sum(1) season_number_coverage,
sum(if(episode_number is null or id = '', 0, 1)) / sum(1) episode_number_coverage,
sum(if(episode_name is null or id = '', 0, 1)) / sum(1) episode_name_coverage,
sum(if(content_length is null or id = '', 0, 1)) / sum(1) content_length_coverage,

from zee_merge

paragraphs.text: %md # Conclusion

msg.data: Conclusion

paragraphs.text:
%md
In ZeeTV
```
* Good cms ID coverage in session summary
* Series/Episode name:
      * session summary do not pass series name, need to extract from asset name.
      * lots of asset name duplications in session summary.
      * CMS provide unique asset name in each cms ID
* Season/Episode number:
      * CMS provide very clean season/episode number but session summary are very dirty
* Content Type:
      * Good quality in both session summary and CMS 
* Genres:
      * CMS provide very clean genre but session summary are very dirty
* Channel:
      * Session summary provide some channel tags, but very dirty. CMS do not have channel tag.
      
* In conclusion: 
      * use CMS to replace customer tags - series/episode name, season/episode number, content type, genres
      * improve channel name accuracy for both integration and MDS rules
```

msg.data:
In ZeeTV

* Good cms ID coverage in session summary
* Series/Episode name:
      * session summary do not pass series name, need to extract from asset name.
      * lots of asset name duplications in session summary.
      * CMS provide unique asset name in each cms ID
* Season/Episode number:
      * CMS provide very clean season/episode number but session summary are very dirty
* Content Type:
      * Good quality in both session summary and CMS 
* Genres:
      * CMS provide very clean genre but session summary are very dirty
* Channel:
      * Session summary provide some channel tags, but very dirty. CMS do not have channel tag.
      
* In conclusion: 
      * use CMS to replace customer tags - series/episode name, season/episode number, content type, genres
      * improve channel name accuracy for both integration and MDS rules
